<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4451] Improve zk node naming (/hbase/shutdown)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4451</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Right now the node &lt;tt&gt;/hbase/shutdown&lt;/tt&gt; is used to indicate cluster status (cluster up, cluster down).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, upon a chat with Lars George today, we feel that having a name &lt;tt&gt;/hbase/shutdown&lt;/tt&gt; is possibly bad. The &lt;tt&gt;/hbase/shutdown&lt;/tt&gt; zknode contains a date when the cluster was &lt;em&gt;started&lt;/em&gt;. Now that is difficult to understand and digest, given that a person may connect to zk and try to look at what it is about (they may think it &apos;shutdown&apos; at that date.).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I feel a better name may simply be: &lt;tt&gt;/hbase/running&lt;/tt&gt;. Thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
